=1>  It is pretty much the same, druids can usually pull off larger multikites but they take longer to finish since their AE's are weaker, overall I think it would be roughly the same.<br> DoT's hardly matters when you are multikiting, they are only good for that desperate finish when you are almost out of mana and by that time you are wasting a lot of time anyway.<br><br> <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR> Evoker<Br> The Circle of Eternity<BR> <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR><i>-I am the romancer. The burning passion that consumes the flesh</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/4/01 8:58:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> I have a Druid friend that was quadding ulthorks at the same time I was. We was gaining EXP at aboput the same rate playing for roughly the same hours. If I understand it, they half to pull with a DOT or SNARE. They get 8 minutes on that snare so they can gather with it. unlike us. They get a pretty good AoE around 34 so they can be pretty effective, but the damage output is REALLY low compared to CoF:<br>Lightning Strike 172-184 @ 149 Mana (1.23) <br>CoF 202 - 216 @ 175 (1.23)<br>Since they have much more time to finish the MOBs tehy can afford the slower output. Add a dot on top of that and they gett slightly more efficient than us.<br>but each kill takes longer so it about evens out.<br><br>Now, If we get creative or into a one-mob-was-tougher situation we generally can manage our way out of that better. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>Learned Slayer, WurmSlayer<BR>Assigner of the Hunt<BR>Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/4/01 9:38:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Most of the time spent in a quadding grind will be meditating (figure 10-12 minutes).  Given this, the differences in kill times is marginal at best, but I've found that Wizards can complete a quad in about 2 minutes on average vs about 4 minutes for a druid.<br><br>There are a couple reasons for this.  Druids must pull with snare, and then gather the mobs together when they are moving at their reduced speed.  Wizards pull and gather at full run speed, then snare with an AE.  Note that druids have an easier time dealing with resists because of the single target nature of their snares.<br><br>Wizard AE's are also more efficient than druid AE's, at least for most level ranges.<br><br>Finally, although wizard snares do not last as long as druid snares, they do have a greater movement reduction.  This is generally balanced by the fact that SoW speed is greater than jboots speed, but slower mobs translates into less running and more nuking.<br><br>Note that dots are generally not more mana efficient than DDs when kiting because of the 2/3 damage rule put in ages ago.  Also, kiting more than 4 at a time generally does not work because the AE's only strike a max of 4 targets.<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/4/01 11:59:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Quad kiting, wizards &gt; druids. If they had to rely on our snare for quadkiting, they would have problems because they take more than twice as long to kill theirs. Yes, single target snare is nice, but there is a lot to be said for doing all 4 at once because grouping them up goes faster. I did the raptors for a number of levels, and if I was sharing the big island, I always made sure that I got to take my 4 first, simply because of the extra amount of time a druid needs to kill theirs. Yah, extra 2 minutes to kill doesn't sound like a lot but it adds up and you are actually gaining XP about 15 percent faster overall. <p>Qaman<BR>Sorcerer - Eternal Wrath<BR>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukazzapkaboom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazzap Kaboom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/8/01 10:44:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> just wondering</span><hr size=1> ok im just wondering if druids get a aesnare or they have to use there lvl 1 (4?) spell to snare it ... also .. what is good to triple (im to scared to quad) at lvl 29? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/01 7:43:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: just wondering</span><hr size=1> Druids have to use their single-target snare (I don't think they get an AoE one ever, if not for a long time).<br><br>Kiting at 29: I've had the best luck with Splitpaw gnolls from the spires, and you can quad them, if the spires are empty.  I normally am only able to grab 2, cause of over-camping of the spires.  Aviaks aren't too bad either, but Avocets have too many HPs for me at 187 INT, so it's gotta be all harriers, which can be a bit rough, too.  Also, Aviaks scatter when they get low - the gnolls don't, which makes them easier again.<br><br>Do NOT do snow cougars in iceclad - they've got WAY to many HPs.  If you find anything else good, let me know.  Best XP I've found at 29 right now tho, is actually groups in Paw.  13% dungeon bonus, plus the 20% group bonus = 1 yellow / hour at least.<br> <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 29th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/01 8:55:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Druids never get an AE snare, but they do get an upgrade at 29 that lasts much longer. <br><br>Level 1: snare -- 15 mana, lasts 1:30<br>Level 29: ensnare -- 35 mana, lasts 10:00<br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/01 9:53:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Actually, they do get an AE snare Armok at level 57, Bonds of Tunare. They also get AE root which we don't and I think that is kind of strange. Their AE snare isn't that good though, especially for Druids given that most of their spells are fairly slow and lower damage than ours, as it only lasts 1:48 (less than Bonds of Force). <p>Qaman<BR>Sorcerer - Eternal Wrath<BR>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/10/01 11:51:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Ah... I had missed the Bonds of Tunare spell.  None of my druid friends ever mentioned it, and looking at the stats, I can see why.  So yes, there is a druid AE, but I guess it's barely worth mentioning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks for keeping me honest Qaman <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Armok Komra &lt;Triton&gt;<br>Sorcerer of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usunsear.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunsear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/01 2:15:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> <br>I've been Quadding for a LONG time.  In my experience, if the blue mobs are readily available, the wizard wins, hands down.  If you need to run around looking for blues, then the druid is going to be ahead every time.  Tracking has it's advantages.  Fundementally Wizard quad kiting is more exciting, nothing like having four mobs full speed on your ass <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>-Xien<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aksel>Aksel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/3/01 9:29:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> Wizards are more mana-efficient in quad kiting generally speaking, the person that said 'if a druid adds in a DOT he's more efficien't is totally off-base, as the mobs he's kiting will be moving, so the DOT will not hit for full damage, hence blowing its efficiency to smithereens.<br><br>-Aksel<br>44 Wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 7:11:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.docsmooth.com/images/me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid vs. Wizard Quad Kiting</span><hr size=1> No, the only Dots that don't hit for full damage on moving MOBs are rains.  Poison and disease based DoTs are effects, they actually stay on the mob if the mob kills the caster, just like spiders used to do to you in WC and NRo when you were 8. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson<br>Wizard of the 29th Season<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 8:09:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicI